This paper presents a data structure for the LCE problem, which is a fundamental problem in string algorithms and data structures. The paper focuses on achieving small space and constant time queries, which are important goals in the field of data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves some information theory and coding theory concepts, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves some complexity theory concepts, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category. The paper presents some trade-off results, which makes cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some combinatorial and graph algorithms concepts, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category.
